Feature Request #134272: Provide a property to determine if a separator should be included after the last element

### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the [existing issues](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues)
- [X] I have read the [guide to filing a bug](https://flutter.dev/docs/resources/bug-reports)

### Use case

There is a situation where I want to display a separator after the last item in ListView.separated. Currently, the separator is only displayed in the gap between the items. I would like to be able to control whether or not the separator is displayed after the last item.

### Proposal

BAD
```Dart
Column(
  children: [
    ListView.separated(
      shrinkWrap: true,
      itemCount: 25,
      separatorBuilder: (BuildContext context, int index) => const Divider(),
      itemBuilder: (BuildContext context, int index) {
        return ListTile(
          title: Text('item $index'),
        );
      },
    ),
    const Divider(),
  ],
);
```

GOOD
```Dart
ListView.separated(
  includeLast: true
  itemCount: 25,
  separatorBuilder: (BuildContext context, int index) => const Divider(),
  itemBuilder: (BuildContext context, int index) {
    return ListTile(
      title: Text('item $index'),
    );
  },
);
```

Community support: 3 reactions (3 upvotes)

Status: shipped/closed

