Plan Item #181700: Proposal: prefer `ValueListenable` over `Animation` in API signatures

[**ValueListenable**](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/foundation/ValueListenable-class.html) is similar to [**Animation**](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/animation/Animation-class.html), but it doesn't have a concept of "forward vs. reverse" so there's no need to implement an animation status.

Sometimes you have a transition that doesn't have an explicit "dismissed" or "completed" state, such as a draggable UI component that moves based on user input. For these cases, your code can be much simpler when you don't use any `Animation` objects:

```dart
class _MyWidgetState extends State<MyWidget> {
  final position = ValueNotifier(Offset.zero);

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return SlideTransition(position: position, child: widget.child);
  }
}
```

In order to make this possible, [**SlideTransition**](https://main-api.flutter.dev/flutter/widgets/SlideTransition-class.html) needs to be tweaked so the `position` field is a `ValueListenable<Offset>` instead of an `Animation<Offset>`.

